The paper presents a new method for training recurrent neural networks, which is a popular topic in the machine learning community. The paper focuses on the optimization problem and stability of the network dynamics, which suggests that it could belong to the sub-categories of cs.LG (Machine Learning), cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing), and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). The paper also mentions phone recognition error on the TIMIT benchmark, which suggests that it could belong to the sub-category of cs.CV (Computer Vision) or cs.SD (Sound).
